"Bunny's Adventures in History": The Time-Traveling Bunny is a web series that follows the adventures of a bunny named Benny as he travels through time, visiting different eras and meeting famous historical figures. Each episode would feature Benny learning about a specific historical event or time period and interacting with people from that time, such as Leonardo da Vinci in the Renaissance or Albert Einstein in the 20th century.

"The Time-Traveling Bunny's Guide to Time Management": In this book, Benny shares his wisdom on how to make the most of your time, using his own experiences traveling through time as examples. The book would cover topics such as prioritizing tasks, avoiding distractions, and making the most of every moment.

"Bunny's Time-Traveling Trivia Challenge": In this game, players take on the role of Benny as he travels through time, answering trivia questions about different historical events and figures. Players can compete against each other or play solo, with the goal of earning the highest score by correctly answering questions and completing challenges.

"The Time-Traveling Bunny's Journal": In this interactive journal, readers can follow Benny's adventures through time, writing their own stories and drawing their own illustrations. The journal includes prompts and activities related to the different time periods Benny visits, such as creating a Renaissance-style painting or writing a letter to a historical figure.

"Bunny's Time-Traveling Adventure Game": In this board game, players take on the role of Benny as he travels through time, visiting different eras and completing challenges to earn points. Players can collect time-traveling gadgets and tools, such as a time-traveling car or a time-traveling device, to help them on their journey. The game can be played with 2-4 players and is suitable for ages 8 and up.
